file2sharepoint (0.3.1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Add EntraIdAppOnlyAuthenticationContext: real Entra ID (Azure AD) v2
    app-only client_credentials authentication for SharePoint, replacing
    the Azure ACS app-only flow (Office365\Runtime\Auth\ClientCredential +
    ClientContext::withCredentials()) Microsoft fully retired for all
    tenants on 2026-04-02 (no extension possible, see
    https://learn.microsoft.com/sharepoint/dev/sp-add-ins/retirement-announcement-for-azure-acs).
    Confirmed empirically: ACS still issues a syntactically valid token, but
    SharePoint Online now rejects it on the real REST call regardless of
    credential correctness. The OFFICE365_USERNAME/OFFICE365_PASSWORD
    user-credential flow is unaffected and unchanged. Uploads now retry
    once on a transient auth failure.
  * bin/azure-setup-wizard: assign the Microsoft Graph "Sites.Selected"
    application permission and perform the per-site grant
    (POST /sites/{siteId}/permissions) instead of the legacy SharePoint
    "AllSites.Write" role, which relied on the same retired ACS model and
    no longer grants working access even when assigned and consented.
  * Migrate the upload itself, for the client-id/secret (app-only) case,
    from classic SharePoint REST (\Office365\SharePoint\ClientContext/
    Folder) to Microsoft Graph's drive API (new GraphSharePointClient,
    GraphApiException). Switching only the token source to Entra ID v2
    (above) was not enough: classic SharePoint REST checks the token's
    appidacr claim and requires appidacr=2 (certificate-based app-only
    auth) - a client_credentials token obtained with a client *secret*
    always has appidacr=1 and is unconditionally rejected with
    "Unsupported app only token.", regardless of Sites.Selected
    permissions granted. Confirmed empirically: the exact same
    token/app/site that gets HTTP 200 from Microsoft Graph gets HTTP 401
    from _api/web/title. See
    https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/microsoftmissioncriticalblog/avoiding-access-errors-with-sharepoint-app-only-access/4459761
    The OFFICE365_USERNAME/OFFICE365_PASSWORD user-credential flow is
    unaffected and keeps using classic REST. The uploaded file's reported
    URL for the app-only case now uses Microsoft Graph's driveItem
    `webUrl` rather than the classic .../download.aspx?SourceUrl=... link
    - both are valid direct links to the file.

 -- Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Tue, 07 Jul 2026 09:00:00 +0200

file2sharepoint (0.3.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add bin/azure-setup-wizard: interactive wizard for Azure App Registration
    setup with automatic az CLI integration, permission assignment and
    client-secret generation
  * Add man pages: file2sharepoint(1) and azure-setup-wizard(1) in docs/
  * Add debian/file2sharepoint.manpages to install man pages into the package
  * Install AppStream metainfo XML to /usr/share/metainfo/ so stock icon
    is resolved by AppStream consumers
  * Install SVG as hicolor scalable stock icon
    io.github.vitexsoftware.file2sharepoint
  * Add <releases> block to AppStream metainfo (fixes pedantic validation)
  * Add make setup-wizard target
